  "title": "Two blocks with lightweight string and pulley",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two blocks attached to either end of a light string that passes over a pulley system, which is at the top of a ramp. Block 1 is shown positioned in the center of the ramp’s incline, and is moving upward and to the right. Block 2 is hanging from the vertical portion of the string and is moving downward.\" height=\"132\" src=\"/images/a0fabba26bfe6abd8692b410aba56b99.png\" width=\"306\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two identical blocks are connected by a lightweight string that passes over a lightweight pulley that can rotate about its axle with negligible friction. The two-block system is released from rest and the blocks accelerate. Which of the following correctly relates the potential energy gained by the block 1-Earth system <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span> to the potential energy lost by the block 2-Earth system <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span> and provides correct evidence?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, equals the absolute value of delta U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, equals the absolute value of delta U sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded><mo>=</mo><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span>, because both blocks travel the same distance.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, equals the absolute value of delta U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, equals the absolute value of delta U sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded><mo>=</mo><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span>, because both blocks gain the same amount of kinetic energy.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, is less than the absolute value of delta U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, is less than the absolute value of delta U sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span>, because the two-block system gains kinetic energy.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, is less than the absolute value of delta U sub 2\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of delta U sub 1, is less than the absolute value of delta U sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded><mo>&lt;</mo><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></math></span></span>, because the tension exerted on block 1 by the string is less than the tension exerted on block 2 by the string.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
